Interface FeatureSubsetSelection

All Superinterfaces:
FeatureSelection
All Known Implementing Classes:
GreedyBackwardElimination, GreedyForwardSelection
public interface FeatureSubsetSelection
extends FeatureSelection

Interface for all attribute subset selection algorithms. An attribute subset selection algorithms consists of two parts. First an attribute evaluation function that score an attribute and second a search algorithm to look for the best combination of attributes.
